"{\"uid\": \"cityam.com-team-gb-at-the-paris-2024-olympics-how-many-medals-will-british-athletes-win\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By:Frank Dalleres  Sports Editor  It's only 20 years since the Athens 2004 Olympic Games, although a look at Team GB's historic medal performance makes it feel like ancient history.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two decades ago British athletes won just nine golds, 30 medals in total and finished in 10th place for the second Olympics in a row.\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 340, \"end\": 347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.994975851753584, \"rank\": 0.004843265383799194, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then Team GB has enjoyed a truly golden era in which they have never come lower than fourth in the medal table.\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 470, \"end\": 477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999758772066007, \"rank\": 1.6207702474206625e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At each of the last three Games, British competitors have won more than 20 golds and surpassed 60 medals in total.\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 611, \"end\": 618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.994975851753584, \"rank\": 0.004843265383799194, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a peak of 29 golds at London 2012 and second place in the medal table at Rio 2016, results tailed off slightly in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 722, \"end\": 733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999944938721612, \"rank\": 5.506096302678643e-06, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 814, \"end\": 819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9672313535567799, \"rank\": 0.033792085139360446, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay in the game with The Turnover: your weekly roundup of sport business news, expert analysis and behind\\u2011the\\u2011scenes stories from City\\u202fAM's sports desk.\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So will their fortunes continue to decline at Paris 2024?\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1023, \"end\": 1033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999947497145, \"rank\": 5.2503058640640455e-09, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or will Team GB bounce back at the closest thing to another home Olympics?\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We examined three rigorously researched medal projections for Team GB in Paris - and the most striking aspect is probably how alike they are.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1173, \"end\": 1180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999758772066007, \"rank\": 1.6207702474206625e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999996384615969, \"rank\": 3.6153864227003367e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"UK Sport, the body responsible for distributing funding, forecasts that British athletes will win between 50 and 70 medals at this summer's Games.\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1254, \"end\": 1262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1326, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.994975851753584, \"rank\": 0.004843265383799194, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB hit that range at each of the last four Olympics, ranging from 51 at Beijing 2008 to 67 in Rio, which set and remains a record.\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1402, \"end\": 1409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999758772066007, \"rank\": 1.6207702474206625e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1479, \"end\": 1491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9926359810594878, \"rank\": 0.007415688401991513, \"text\": \"Beijing 2008\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1501, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9994052172452086, \"rank\": 0.0005951367193758357, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the forecast sounds a little vague, it may be because a bigger range gives UK Sport more leeway to argue that they hit their target.\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1617, \"end\": 1625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Next we looked at two independent projections, the first of which was compiled by advisory behemoth PwC.\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"PwC says its model takes into account not only performance at past Olympics but also demographic and economic size, and income levels.\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1782, \"end\": 1785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PricewaterhouseCoopers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"PwC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PricewaterhouseCoopers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PricewaterhouseCoopers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its forecast is very specific and has Team GB winning 54 medals, of which 20 are gold.\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1956, \"end\": 1963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999758772066007, \"rank\": 1.6207702474206625e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is down on the last three Games but better than Beijing 2008 and its predecessors.\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2092, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, that tally would place Britain fifth in the table, behind the US, China, Japan and France - the team's worst finish since Athens 2004.\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2237, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2126, \"end\": 2133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.981718376531369, \"rank\": 0.018620184316834584, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2165, \"end\": 2167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9994255248755928, \"rank\": 0.000466045484102839, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2169, \"end\": 2174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9807067139369415, \"rank\": 0.016978537956133886, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2176, \"end\": 2181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9902255136628578, \"rank\": 0.005120468887459976, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2186, \"end\": 2192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9044090587368101, \"rank\": 0.09705828121441923, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other independent analysis we examined was carried outby Gracenote, an arm of media analysis giant Nielsen.\", \"from\": 2239, \"to\": 2350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gracenote\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gracenote\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gracenote\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gracenote\"}, {\"begin\": 2342, \"end\": 2349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nielsen_Holdings\", \"score\": 0.9900794168953181, \"rank\": 0.007930611294491198, \"text\": \"Nielsen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nielsen_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nielsen_Holdings\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its Virtual Medal Table forecasts just 17 golds for Team GB, which would be their lowest total since 2004, albeit nearly double the Athens figure.\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2404, \"end\": 2411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999758772066007, \"rank\": 1.6207702474206625e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2484, \"end\": 2490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998922148368591, \"rank\": 0.00010779675275612009, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gracenote predicts British athletes will win 63 medals for the fourth Games in a row.\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2519, \"end\": 2526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.994975851753584, \"rank\": 0.004843265383799194, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Until London 2012, this had not been achieved for more than a century.\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2592, \"end\": 2603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999944938721612, \"rank\": 5.506096302678643e-06, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With gold count determining medal table position, that would see Team GB repeat their fourth-place finish from last time in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2788, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2723, \"end\": 2730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999758772066007, \"rank\": 1.6207702474206625e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2782, \"end\": 2787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9672313535567799, \"rank\": 0.033792085139360446, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Share this article  Subscribe to the City AM newsletter to have our top stories delivered directly to your inbox.\", \"from\": 2790, \"to\": 2903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow us for breaking news and latest updates\", \"from\": 2905, \"to\": 2951, \"entities\": []}]}"